message.content:
cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the relationship between robot attributes and human trust in robots, and involves the use of two robots in an interaction game.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper focuses on the human perception of robots and their interaction with them.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of anthropomorphism in robots, which is a common technique in AI to make machines more relatable to humans.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper involves the design and implementation of an interaction game on two robots.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve the use of machine learning techniques to analyze the data collected from the interaction game.
